# The analytics stack (on S3)

Four services around Redshift, all on the **S3 data lake**.

## Athena — serverless SQL on S3

No infra / loading; SQL over S3 objects (Glue Catalog), **per-TB scanned**. For log / ad-hoc / lake queries when a warehouse is overkill.
**vs. Spectrum:** Athena standalone · Spectrum = part of Redshift. **No Redshift → Athena; have it → Spectrum.**

## Glue — ETL + Data Catalog

**Crawlers** infer S3 schemas → the **Catalog** (Athena / Spectrum / EMR all read it). **Glue ETL** = serverless Spark (per DPU-sec).

## EMR & OpenSearch

- **EMR** — managed **Hadoop / Spark** (Hive, Presto, HBase) — custom / heavy big-data
- **OpenSearch** — **full-text search + log analytics** (+ Dashboards). Common: **DynamoDB Streams → OpenSearch**.
